title: Simply connected space
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

A topological space $$X$$ is called //simply connected// if it is path-connected and $$\pi_1(X,x_0)$$ is trivial for any $$x_0 \in X.$$

@@.theorem
''Proposition.''
$$X$$ is simply connected if and only if for any $$a,b \in X,$$ there is a unique homotopy class of paths form $$a$$ to $$b.$$